I wish Spring Break would get here NOW!!! ahhhhhh!! BUT going home a week from tomorrow!!!!!!!!



:-D

I was just looking through photo albums, I miss those times with high school peeps.

It's been three months, three fucking months!!!!!!!!

It's ridiculous how I am still in love with him, want so badly to be with him. Its not just a period where I want to be with anyone, I want to be with him.

I love him, and I wish that I didnt. Is there anyway that I can erase my memories of him?

Lyrics by my friend Becki:

To the guys who made me smile
You're the ones who mattered for a while
But to the man who made me cry
You'll be in my heart until the day I die



yeah .... 

xoxo 
Kelly

As of today I am officially an alumnus of Walt Whitman High School. Everything feels so different when you are the one graduating. I still have a hard time realizing that I am now in college. *all smiles*

In shaving before work today, so I would look all pretty, I shaved off 1/2 of SKIN on my right ankle. This ended all hopes of Kelly having pretty ankles for teh summer.

*pout* and it is blood under the bandage, and not purdy. And it hurts. Someone blow it a kiss to make it go away?

I had work orientation today, much fun, learned how to do transactions on the register and to ring up stuff and do gift cards and all that jazz. Got to watch a video on our products in the store and saw the stock room and break room. There was old school boy bands and Old Christina Aguilera and Brit Spears playing at work today. 

Starting on Sunday I think! *excited* any of ya'll feel like coming to see me, its at MontgomerY Mall at Bath and Body Works

I'm Fantine!
Though I mean well, my trusting nature gets me into appalling amounts of trouble. Still, I do my best to get through, and I would do absolutely anything for my loved ones.

CLASS OF 2004!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

OMG OMG this is teh coolest. Graduation on Thursday, and my drivers liscense on Wednesday. 

Our pool picnic was today and Sam and I messed with cicadas. I used the cotten candy cone (after I had eaten the cotton candy) to pick up the cicadas and we tried to put them on the fence. They did not like the cotton candy and tried to fly away

The life and times of an 18 year old..........torturing cicadas....they only come out every 17 years, so they subject themselves to torture........................but not decapitation!!!!!!!!!! I saw two halves of a cicada lying on the gravel and it made me sad.

>

Wow..........senior exams start on Monday. And my last day is on Friday. I feel sort of weird, like I am ready, but like I am constantly on edge. It's like my stomach is in one big knot over what will happen next. It is totally new and different and I am not really sure I am ready for it.

And I will miss all my WWHS peeps so much!!!!!!!!!! We must party over the summer. What say you all?

Senior Toga Day is tomorrow!!!!!!!!!! And my toga is my brother's old bedsheet, which is blue, light blue, and very cool. I always figure if it is incredibly cold tomorrow, I can always remove the toga and wrap the sheet around myself in order to stay warm.

Come see the last night of the Festival of the Arts!!!!!!!

Funny/ gross story today in Physics. We were doing a lab on electrostatic charges that didn't work that well considering that it is humid as ever outside. And the AC in the school in broken. *grumble grumble...evil MoCo....grumble grumble*

Michelle (lab partner) went to go get an extra piece of fur to charge the Strofoam with and she came back and screamed Oh my God Mr. Feinberg our fur still has a FOOT! And it did. And it was very very upsetting

We settled for making people's hair stand on end. Ezra's hair (the Jewfro) and David and Josh and Adam and me, red hair has some special qualities we hoped, only to be proven wrong.

What is your life rated?
Great stuff right here. Yeah so I am moving my journal-ness to www.xanga.com the username is ShinyLights stalk if you will...I will keep this for the purpose of stalking you all, I do it cause I love ya'll.

Went to Senior Banquet last night
Gawd it was much fun (look! I am becoming like Paige! I say Gawd - loverface rocks)
I went with Whitney, Kelly Olive and Harriet and we had fun.....looked awesomely hot. Since Harriet's family are diplomats, they have a driver and the driver took us to the banquet *squee*
There was dancing, dinner (FOOD!!! - and salad, i am such a salad whore), SENIOR video (so funny, class reunion theme), and superlatives (preps got most of everything - I do *not* think Kathern Leas should have gotten sex symbol, she only got it b/c she a popular lil bitch)

Dancing was my favorite part, mo def. Dude...........my dress that I wore has side slits that you can adjust the lenght of. I danced like a lil slut for a while ;) Then I toned it down, then danced like a lil slut again...good times. I will post pics laterz from the Banquet.

o.O and I have a group for Prom! We have like 10 or 15 couples and it is gonna be just the coolest night in the world... we should so get one of those Hummer limos, tacky as hell but how else are we gonna fit 30 people into one limo?!

Pics laterz mi chicos y chicas!

So why is it that computers don't work when you need them to?
Annoyance......hopefully I am getting close to figuring things out. Technology and me are not good friends...more like good enemies x_X

Today was good ^.^ We did not get yelled at in choir like yesterday, seems like finally some people are starting to get their butts in gear *hopes*.
o.O the Japanese exchange students came on Saturday for two weeks! 'Tis very exciting...they come to school for lunch and the last two periods of the day and I know a bunch of people who are hosting.
The boys go off tomorrow to compete in robot fighting thing, and they keep insisting that they are going to die. If their robot dies, I hope it dies creativly, like fighting with another robot, much like Battlebots. That would be fun to see.
Alex has a girlfriend and was being all deceptive about it, but we finally found out the truth! Heh, they are so cute together....very much like Rachel and Alex, Bekki and Greg....I wanna be cute like that with *someone*

o.O big news! I think I may have found my prom dress. It is from Brass Plum and is bronze color, but not shiny, kinda hard to describe, but I will post a pic as soon as I can!!!
I gots to go finish some homework and then take a shower and crawl into bed.
bai!
Good luck to Orchestra in Festival tomorrow!

Sitting here doing homework, coloring maps for AP Euro, such great work for high schoolers, I realize how much I miss coloring XD

I have a Physics test tomorrow, and I am worried, we only have two formulas to mess with although they get twisted in all kinds of ways and end up deriving all these new formulas. There are so many things to remember...and what is with the omega stuff?! Ah well...I can only do the best that I can, and I will certainly try my hardest to achieve that. Choir had festival on Tuesday and it went alright, the judges were pretty hard on everyone, although it was for the good of the group and we needed those comments in order to do well in Boston and at states. We got a mixture of one's and two's, but all of the comments were totally true. Damn we are too white ^.^
Before competition, "Reverend Reyvie" preached to the choir (literally) and got us pumped up

FOR THE FIRST TIME IN WHITMAN HISTORY, CHOIR EARNED A PERFECT SCORE IN SIGHTREADING!!!!!!!! THAT'S 28/28
YAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
